 I'm also X in this board. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2012<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/1/02 3:14:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> Sounds groovy. Plenty of nuclear missiles and atomic bomb propelled spacecraft I hope. Nerva's, inertia weapons and not too much emphasis on arguably near future nasties like nanobots and fusion. Predicting technology breakthroughs is an inexact science at best. Plenty of incredible state of the art stuff around now that would prove interesting within the unconfined spaces between planets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkmatter>darkmatter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/1/02 8:06:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> I've had enough of &quot;real war&quot;. I would hope there would be enough room and resources with a space faring culture to prevent the hate and resource competition that exists on the limited biosphere of Earth. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=x>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/1/02 2:16:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> Just repeat to yourself it's just a messageboard.  You really should relax <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkmatter>darkmatter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/2/02 7:52:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> I am relaxed. I intend no insult or inflammatory remark. Its just that those who have seen actual combat have no use for playacting such horrors. Get me off this limited biosphere! I'd be happier terraforming an asteroid or operating a multigenerational interstellar craft.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=x>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/6/02 1:50:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Darkmatter</span><hr size=1> Let me ask you this: were you in the military and did you see any action during active duty?  Just curious. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hamster>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/6/02 3:34:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/pubimage.asp?id_=638250 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> I think Darkmatter's viewpoints might be common among vets.  I knew a WWII vet that refused to watch war movies and didn't particularly care to indulge in the details even though I was always pestering him to.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkmatter>darkmatter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/7/02 7:10:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> Yes, I am a Vet. and no, I won't give details and anyone else with similer experiences won't talk except maybe to another person that can empathize with a common experience. The problem you see, is that trying to explain to someone without the worldveiw that life experiences create just confuses the nub and frustrates/angers the &quot;old fart&quot; (me).<br>
Enough lecture, lets go solar sailing to Ganameade.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=x>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/7/02 11:06:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> darkmatter, the same argument could be made by a divorcee about a movie like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The War of the Roses</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or any cop about all of the cops shows on TV.  There's nothing wrong with incorporating elements from real life into fiction even if it's negative. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2019<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/7/02 6:42:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> War isn't about resources. It's about power. Power being tied up with keeping others down. Todays world is still fueled by slavery and bullcrap. We just use different terms to describe these all too present things. The West is supported on the shoulders of the developing World. I mean this as no insult to the West. It's just the way of things and I'm a reali